The project:
- represents a Github/Gitea action for increasing versions on a monno/multi repo project
- is written with NodeJs (ES6 / ESM), using JSDoc for documentation
- it is tested using Vitest

Code needs to be written:
- respecting KISS and DRY principles
- as unitary as possible (simple functions, easy to test, easy to read and understand) as human readable as possible
- respecting Uncle Bob's clean code principles
- using functional programming

DO NOT:
- remove commented code, unless told so; sometimes, to better understand the code step I am analyzing, I am commenting the rest of the code around it
